>
<br>
But as Hippolyte's body began to come back to life, no nectar of the Gods could help Aly. Her body was like ice and her souless eyes were still open.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http:// http://ausxip.com/screengrabs/season5/01-fallen_angel/fa1360.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
a few wolves entered the hut and lay down next to Aly's body as they began to whine aloud. As the spirit of the Atmah watched over the scene, she knew that this was not for either of the amazon queens.<br>
<br>
*~* Gabrielle ~*~ The atmah spoke to her child. <br>
~*~ Gabrielle only yours and Hippolyte's love can bring her spirit back. It will be hard for Alysia, for she consists of two spirits and both need to be brought back. Her own as well as Samsara's.~*~<br>
<br>
The Atmah frowned and then disappeared.<br>
<br>
Alysia's body lay there, cold and lifeless. The Amazons had managed to remove the spear, but her body was covered in blood.<br>
<br>
